Add detailed documentation for MySQL group commit process
This commit introduces a comprehensive markdown document outlining the group commit mechanism in MySQL, specifically focusing on the ordered_commit() function and its interaction with various stages such as FLUSH_STAGE, SYNC_STAGE, and COMMIT_STAGE. The document includes a flowchart representation of the process, detailing the steps involved in transaction handling, flushing logs, and committing changes to the storage engine. This addition aims to enhance understanding of the internal workings of MySQL's transaction management and binlog handling.
